data.text:
###Structure of an Essay

Title
Introduction
Body
Main or subsidiary point
Support for said points
Background material
Illustrations or examples
Reasons
Suggesting purposes
Supporting Conclusions
Giving Explanations
Transitions
Conclusion

Title and introduction should be closely related

###Writing checklist
Is every sentence complete, not a fragment?
Do the subject and predicate agree in number in each sentence?
is every word spelled correctly?
Are words capitalised properly?
Does each pronoun unambiguously refer to its antecedent?
Do you stay in the same tense and person throughout?
Are all words used correctly?

###Elements of good writing
Clarity - using clear and unambiguous language
Cohesion - Linking everything in the text to the topic, having a clear connection with all of the text
Focus - Establishes what you are writing about and why

###SLOOWER
Select a topic
List your ideas
Organise your ideas
Outline your essay
Write your first draft
Edit your first draft
Rewrite your essay

###PEEL
Point 
Explain 
Evaluate and 
Link
